posts.cooked:
Hi we have a current problem with rev items we want to assign new can id of the spark max devices but the spark max are not shown on rev hardware client besides of that we have an ongoing problem with pdh with status lights are not turning on and channel lights not turning off even though we connect breaker

This is our e board for testing spark maxes one of them showing that there is no motor connected which is normal I didn’t connect one of them giving gate fault and rest of them giving coast signal but I cannot say the same thing with PDH some channel lights turn off even though we didn’t connect controller and status light always off I tried to connect spark max and pdh with usb to the computer but I cannot still see the products on REV Hardware Client

posts.name: Tayler Uva
posts.cooked: Have you connected to the Sparks via USB C cable to your laptop?

posts.name: Hüseyin Arda Çavdar
posts.cooked: I connected trough usb c and it didn’t show up in Rev Hardware Client

posts.name: Domtech
posts.cooked:
How are the CAN wires connected here? Are there 3 pairs of CAN wires connected to the PDP ? It should be the last device in the chain and only have one pair of wires connected to it. The jumper in the PDP should also be set to enable the termination resistor.

Kalimbus:

I didn’t connect one of them giving gate fault

A gate driver fault is normal if a motor is not connected.

Kalimbus:

problem with rev items we want to assign new can id of the spark max devices but the spark max are not shown on rev hardware client

My recommendation is to disconnect them from the CAN network and set their unique IDs one at a time over USB before connecting them together. If they still aren’t showing up in software with just the USB connected then I would talk to REV support.

Also what is going on with the main power connections? That doesn’t look right. What are those blue parts?

posts.name: Hüseyin Arda Çavdar
posts.cooked:

I am trying to connect with usb but it doesn’t show up on hardware client

We are not going to use pdp in our robot it is only for assigning can id’s so it is for shor time
